npc/wira: This is as far as I can take you. Beyond this gate is the thing that runs all of it — the House.
npc/wira: Before you face it, I have to be sure you understand what winning actually means here.
npc/wira: You do not beat the House at its game. The game is rigged — that was the first thing you learned. You beat it by walking away, and by helping others walk away too.
npc/wira: So carry this out with you, past the fight, into the real world.
npc/wira: If gambling has its hooks in you or someone you love, help is real and it is close. In Indonesia, call 119 extension 8 — the mental-health and addiction line. Free. Confidential. No judgement.
npc/wira: Report the apps and sites at aduankonten.id so they reach fewer people. Every one taken down is someone spared.
npc/wira: And recovery is possible. People rebuild — the savings, the sleep, the trust. It starts with one honest conversation and one refusal to play.
npc/wira: Now, one last set of questions. There is no skipping this one. Answer them all correctly and the gate opens.
npc/wira: Miss one and that's fine — we go again until it's clear. This lesson matters more than the fight ever will.
